China Mobile’s Wang Says Apple’s Steve Jobs ‘Defined the Future’

-- B y   M a r k   L e e
-- 
2011-10-06T09:10:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-06/china-mobile-s-wang-says-apple-s-steve-jobs-defined-the-future-.html
Wang Jianzhou, chairman of  China
Mobile Ltd. (941) , comments on the death of  Apple Inc. (AAPL)  Chairman Steve Jobs.  Wang has sent a letter to Apple expressing condolences,
according to an e-mailed statement today by China Mobile, the
country’s biggest wireless carrier.  “Steve Jobs had an extraordinary spirit of innovation,
which has won the respect of his colleagues. Under his
leadership, Apple didn’t just become a popular consumer brand,
but also defined the future of the industry.  “Steve Jobs’s passing is a great loss for the industry. He
perfectly combined technology with practical usability, an
achievement that is the goal of all practitioners in the
technology and telecommunications industry.  His passion and his enthusiasm made a lasting impression on
me when we met.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Mark Lee  in Hong Kong at 
 wlee37@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Young-Sam Cho at   ycho2@bloomberg.net  